            <br />
            <h5>Definitions – EMIS SNAP SURVEY</h5>
            <hr />
            <section id="what-we-do" class="what-we-do">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-6 d-flex">
                            <div class="icon-box" style="text-align:left">
                                <table class="table table-bordered">
                                    <thead>
                                        <tr>
                                            <th>Term</th>
                                            <th>Explanation</th>
                                        </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Concessions</td>
                                            <td>means measures put in place by the employer to accommodate employees who have comorbidities, or who are 60 years of age with other underlying health conditions that places them at risk to be infected by COVID-19 for the duration of Alert levels 3 and 2 of the of the National State of Disaster as provided for in Collective Agreement 1 of 2020.</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Daily Rotation</td>
                                            <td>refers to a system of rotation of learners in which alternating days per week are used groups/grades of learners, for example, Grades 10 and 11 come in on Monday, Wednesday and Fridays and Grades 8 and 9 on Tuesdays and Thursdays</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Enrolment</td>
                                            <td>refers to the total number of learners registered at the school for a particular academic year.</td>
                                        </tr>
                                         <tr>
                                            <td>Home Education</td>
                                            <td>means a purposeful programme of education for a learner, alternative to school attendance, which:
(a) is provided under the direction and supervision of the learner’s parent primarily in the environment of the learner’s home and approved by the Head of Department;
(b) may include tutorial or other educational support if necessary, secured by the parent on specific areas of the curriculum followed by the learner; and
(c) meets the requirements for registration of a learner for home education contemplated in Section 51 of the South African Schools Act,1996.
</td>
                                        </tr>
                                         <tr>
                                            <td>Hybrid </td>
                                            <td>Refers to a mix model of daily and weekly rotation</td>
                                        </tr>
                                         <tr>
                                            <td>Lockdown Learning</td>
                                            <td>means a partial or conditional form of home-based learning available to learners that have comorbidities or are fearful or anxious about being infected with the coronavirus.  Parents must apply to the Department and receive approval for learners to have access to Lockdown Learning. This type of learning takes place online or remotely and requires the parents to pick up material from the school fortnightly.</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Platooning </td>
                                            <td>means two separate sets of pupils use the same school building, one set in the morning and the other set in the afternoon, for example, Grades 1 to 3 in the morning and Grades 4 to 6 in the afternoon.</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Potential Drop-Outs</td>
                                            <td>refers to those learners that have not returned to school since the reopening of schools and excludes learners that are registered with the Department for Lockdown Learning.</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Personal Protective Equipment (PPE)</td>
                                            <td>means any device or appliance designed to be worn or held by an individual for protection against one or more health and safety hazards e.g. masks, gloves, face shields, etc.</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Remote learning</td>
                                            <td>refers to a situation where a learner and the educator, or information source, are not physically present in a traditional classroom environment. Information is relayed through learner activity packs, technology, such as discussion boards, video conferencing and online platforms.</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Weekly Rotation</td>
                                            <td>refers to a system of rotation of learners in which groups/grades of learners attending school on alternate weeks, for example, Week 1 – Grades 10 and 11, Week 2 - Grades 8 and 9, etc.</td>
                                        </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                </table>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
